overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and an existing Statement of
  Work. The primary goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to
  implement any missing functionalities. The agent conducted a thorough code
  review, identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent proceeded
  to implement these missing features. Key additions included a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness, which triggers urgent safety warnings for high scores,
  and sophisticated detection logic for complex sleep disorders like COMISA
  (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, complete
  with tailored recommendations. The agent also integrated a new "Resources &
  Next Steps" section with placeholder outbound links to relevant external
  resources and implemented a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness. These changes were applied consistently across both the
  interactive web report and the generated PDF report, significantly enhancing
  the application's diagnostic capabilities and user guidance.
